	<body>
        
		<section>
			<h1>Welcome to the Behavioural Questions RESTful API Guide</h1>
			<p>Records will be in the following JSON format:</p>
			<code>
                {</br> "_id": a unique ID Number, in BSON format allocated automatically.</br>
                "question": a String which poses the question you want to ask.
                ,</br> "values": An array of strings with
				leadership values [], </br>}
			</code>
		</section>
        <aside>
            <nav>
                <h3>Behavioural Recruitment API</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="/">RESTful API Guide</a></li>
                   <li><a href="/list">Generate Question List</a></li>
                   <li><a href="/newQuestion">Submit a new Question</a></li>
                </ul>
            </nav>
          </aside>
		<section>
			<h2>Accessing the API</h2>
            <h2>Return a Random Question</h2>
			<a href="https://behavioural-recruitment.thewoodenman.repl.co/questions/random/pickone"><span>https://behavioural-recruitment.thewoodenman.repl.co/questions/random/pickone</span></a></br>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Return a Question by ObjectId</h2>
            <span>Send a GET request to https://behavioural-recruitment.thewoodenman.repl.co/questions/{id}</span></br>
			<span>replacing {id} in the URI with the ObjectId of your target question</span></br>
			<span>Object Ids are in the standard BSON format, you can find them specifically from other searches.</span></br>
 		</section>
         <section>
            <h2>Return a Question by a Single Value</h2>
            <span>Send a GET request to https://behavioural-recruitment.thewoodenman.repl.co/questions/values/{value}</span></br>
			<span>replacing {value} in the URI with your target leadership value in string format</span></br>
			<span>Object Ids are in the standard BSON format.</span></br>
 		</section>
        <section>
            <h2>
                Submit a Question
            </h2>
            <span>Send a POST request to https://behavioural-recruitment.thewoodenman.repl.co/questions/addone</span></br>
            <span>Omit the ObjectId in the JSON as these will be allocated automatically, </span></br>
            <span>Include the new question in JSON format correctly in the format displayed above.</span></br>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>
                Submit many Questions
            </h2>
            <span>Send a POST request to https://behavioural-recruitment.thewoodenman.repl.co/questions/addmany</span></br>
            <span>Omit the ObjectId in the JSON as these will be allocated automatically, </span></br>
            <span>Include the new question in JSON format correctly in a different format to the one above, specifically: </span></br>
            <br>
            <pre><code>
                { "array" :[{
                    "question":
                        "{Insert Question Text Here}",
                    "values": [value1, value2, value3]
                },
                {
                    "question":
                        "{Insert Question Text 2 Here}",
                    "values": [value1, value2, value3]
                }]}
            </code></pre>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>
                Replace a Question
            </h2>
            <span>Send a POST request to https://behavioural-recruitment.thewoodenman.repl.co/questions/{id}/replace</span></br>
            <span>replacing {id} in the URI with the ObjectId of your target question</span></br>
            <span>submit your replacement question in JSON format as the body of the POST request</span></br>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>
                Replace the values of a Question
            </h2>
            <span>Send a POST request to https://behavioural-recruitment.thewoodenman.repl.co/questions/{id}/values/replace</span></br>
            <span>replacing {id} in the URI with the ObjectId of your target question</span></br>
            <span>submit your replacement values in JSON format, but as a series of strings within an array.</span>
            <span> as the body of the POST request</span></br>

            <code>{ "values": ["optimistic",
                "results oriented",
                "sense of humour",
                "speed",
                "versatility"]
            }</code>
        </section>
